## Context

I'm running `pnpm --filter @electron-template/desktop dev` after upgrading to electron-vite 5.0.0. The dev server starts, then immediately exits with `Error: Cannot find module 'electron-vite/dist/index.mjs'`.

## Detailed repro

I added a custom plugin to `apps/desktop/electron.vite.config.ts`:

```ts
import { defineConfig } from "electron-vite";
import react from "@vitejs/plugin-react";

export default defineConfig({
  main: {
    plugins: [react()],
  },
  preload: {
    plugins: [react()],
  },
  renderer: {
    plugins: [react()],
    resolve: {
      alias: {
        "@": new URL("./src", import.meta.url).pathname,
      },
    },
  },
});
```

## Error

```
[ERROR] Error: Cannot find module 'electron-vite/dist/index.mjs'
    at Function.Module._resolveFilename (node:internal/modules/cjs/loader:1231:15)
    at Function.resolve (node:internal/modules/esm/loader:387:28)
    at /Users/me/projects/complete-electron-template/apps/desktop/electron.vite.config.ts:1:15
```

## Things I've tried

- Removed `node_modules/.cache`
- Re-installed with `pnpm install --force`
- Confirmed `electron-vite/dist/index.mjs` exists at `node_modules/electron-vite/dist/index.mjs`

## Environment

```
Node 22.13.0
pnpm 9.0.0
eOS 14.4
electron-vite 5.0.0 (upgraded from 4.x)
```
